   About Technology Risk, Audit & Compliance (TRAC)
   We are an exceptional team of professionals who bring a systematic and
   disciplined approach to evaluating and improving the effectiveness of
   our technology risk profile, operational controls and governance
   processes. With Trust as our #1 value, our mission is to ensure
   Salesforce.com is always the secure and trusted enterprise cloud
   provider.
   Analyst, Technology Risk Audit & Compliance (Public Sector)
   Salesforce.com is looking for an experienced and innovative compliance
   analyst located in Herndon, VA that has a deep understanding of federal
   government compliance (FISMA, FedRAMP), the ability to understand IT
   processes, effectively communicate salesforce.comâs technology and
   security controls, and drive innovative process changes throughout the
   organization to maintain compliance with public sector requirements.
   This role is part of the Compliance Team, reports directly to the
   Senior Manager of TRAC (Public Sector), and is primarily a role
   supporting compliance needs of public sector customers.
   TRAC values strong cross-team communication & collaboration and is
   looking for a motivated and collaborative candidate that can work
   across teams to build consensus, resolve conflicts, and create positive
   long term working relationships. You should also be able to work in a
   quickly changing environment and be able to represent TRAC to our
   customers as well as our internal leadership.
   The successful candidate will have experience translating complex
   topics and technical controls to a non-technical audience, have the
   ability to respond to security questionnaires, represent salesforce.com
   to customers, and align the business to support public sector
   requirements. This requires an individual with proven self-direction,
   self-confidence, and high energy.
   The successful candidate will also demonstrate a history of combining a
   bias for execution with the ability to analyze complex problems, think
   creatively, communicate recommendations, influence change, and drive
   the just the right amount of process and structure in an extremely
   dynamic environment.
   Key Responsibilities:
     * Support public sector compliance audits, continuous monitoring, and
       drive remediation activities to ensure ongoing compliance.
     * Accountable for monitoring and testing the effectiveness of our
       compliance activities, provide key feedback on potential issues and
       trends, and escalate when appropriate.
     * Understand salesforce.com's control environment and operating model
       and how it continues to change and evolve over time.
     * Communicate to internal customers the specific controls the team or
       process owner is responsible for.
     * Be a trusted and knowledgeable resource for our customers in the
       areas of compliance, information security, and industry standards.
     * Accurately represent salesforce.com in customer facing meetings,
       calls, and in security questionnaires to support customer audits,
       sales, and ongoing compliance.
     * Help our customers understand salesforce.com's security controls
       and the appropriate certifications and compliance objectives
       related to the operation of a cloud environment.
     * Evaluate new public sector requirements and determine the impact to
       existing business practices and customer compliance requirements.
     * Understand and support existing IT security certification
       initiatives and corresponding security processes.
     * Provide feedback on the company's compliance framework to
       continuous improve our Information Security Management System.

   Skills & Experience [Required]:
     * University degree (IT/IS related field preferred).
     * Minimum 2-3 years experience in IT security, compliance, consulting
       or other business advisory role.
     * Experience with information security controls, methodologies, and
       practices.
     * Extensive knowledge of U.S. public sector compliance requirements
       (FISMA, FedRAMP).
     * Good working knowledge of IT security control frameworks (NIST
       800-53 Rev. 3, ISO 27001, PCI-DSS, SOX).
     * Strong analytical and problem solving skills and the ability to
       âthink-out-of-the-boxâ.
     * Excellent written and verbal communication (including public
       speaking) and interpersonal skills that enable positive influence
       for Salesforce.com with customers.
     * Has experience with information security or compliance and uses
       professional concepts and company objectives to resolve complex
       issues in creative and effective ways.
     * Determines methods and procedures on new assignments, and may
       provide guidance to others.
     * Ability to travel up to 10%.

   Skills & Experience [Desired]:
     * Advanced degree.
     * Pursuing relevant professional certifications such as CISSP, CISM,
       CISA, GIAC, or CAIS.
     * Knowledge about cloud computing businesses and processes.
     * Hands-on experience using Salesforce products.
     * Experience working directly with auditors.
     * Familiarity with the Federal Information Security Management Act
       (FISMA), Federal Risk and Authorization Management Program
       (FedRAMP), National Institute of Standards and Technologies (NIST),
       Payment Card Industry (PCI), Sarbanes-Oxley (SOX) and other
       relevant policies, regulations, and standards.
     * Experience developing metrics to measure IT process effectiveness
       and consistency.
     * Involved in external compliance and security organizations.

